The paper discusses using Graph Neural Networks for supervised learning on relational databases, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.DB (Databases) sub-category. Additionally, the paper focuses on machine learning and feature engineering, which are topics commonly found in the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories. The use of Graph Neural Networks also suggests that the paper could belong to the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-category. Finally, the paper could also belong to the cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category, as it discusses the potential loss of relational structure in data during feature engineering.
